Would you pay $500,000 for a bottle of Red?

Does a more expensive wine mean a better wine?


Expensive Wines vs. Affordable Wines

According to Finances Online the most expensive wine in the world is the Screaming Eagle Cabernet 1992 which was sold at the Napa Valley Auction in 2000 for $500,000. We understand this relatively young wine is way too expensive to be use in a day to days
